\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you give me your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Frank Lyle Victor Waldegrave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 435 Canterbury Street, Gilingham, Kent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And you're a married man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I should think so. Very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you tell me what year you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. August the fifteenth 1915, on a Sunday. Which is our - our anniversary is a fortnight's time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And the year you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I was born day after my wedding - I mean in 1890 - in 1892. August the sixteenth 1892.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you tell me where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, I was born in the parish of St Mary Stratton, Portsmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How many years did you live in that house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh - I was - moved from there when I was a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I don't know really because I - my mother was a daughter of a Naval - Naval officer who h
ad transferred at the time - my father was a local employed dockyard worker and my mother had gone up to her parents in Wales and took us and I think when they returned from there they found a new house or new home for us to go to. In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ortsmouth. In - in t
he same area really. But - came back to Portsmouth so I could have been anything I suppose perhaps eighteen months-two years old when I left that first house. But came back into the same area so it doesn't really signify a thing from the point of view of 
addresses because they may not even exist now anyway. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How long were you in Wales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh only - only a short while. About - perhaps a year - nine months or a year perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Holyhead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was that with relations in Wales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, no, my mother you see. That's where my mother - I was a child in arms when you've got to visualize that, and therefore I have not the slightest recollection whom we stopped with but - you know what I mean for some lodgings or - accom}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 mo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 dation of some sort my grandfather found for - for my mother at that period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Then you moved back to Portsmouth, somewhere near where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes, now of course we can come back to that now in a more substantial manner in as much as I lived i
n this area for about - eight - nine years. Yes, about eight years. And we moved to the outskirts of Portsmouth which was rather rural at that time, a place called Millton, on the outskirts of Portsmouth that is now all embodied into Portsmouth as a whole
 
but - that particular movement took me into a - a sphere of life totally different more or less from what I was you see, in as much that as a child - going to school there, in the original home and then going out into this rural area, coming from that - I
 had to come into Portsmouth again to another school which was nearer to my new residence - my way of life was changed as a child from being - what can I say - more or less a street }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 arab}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  or that sort of thing of playing round the streets and so forth into and becoming acquaintable with the countryside and - amateur cho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
rboy in the old Milton church which doesn't exist any more and - also I - began to play football. Just prior to that I decided to learn to smoke, I - I had fag, that's - that's one of my - one
 of my bad points. Yes. But then - that - that was until I was - until June 1903. That happened in the 1902/03. I was just ten and bordering on eleven years of age at that time we moved from there to Plymouth. Our first transitional move. But during - may
 
I say this - during my early days in - as a child - in Portsmouth I had one - we - my - my brother and I, we have one very outstanding, what can I say - look - on thing we looked forward to and regularly every summer holiday was spent with our grandparent
s at Cowes in the Isle of Wight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How old were you when you went to Milton from Portsmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Near enough I suppose, nine - eight - eight - between eight and nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So you weren't many years in Milton?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, before we moved - moved away
 from - my father went abroad you see - to - to the Cape and when he came back he was transferred from Portsmouth docky rd to Plymouth }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ackyard which was the Naval - the Naval town, of course, you'd probably know all about that anyway. Well - anyway - when
 he - he she promotion with in his own sphere, there was no vacancy when he came home from the Cape at his home baged yard so he had to choose between Devonport dockyard and Shoerness dockyard, that's where the two vacancies - vacancies were and he should
 
have chose Devonport dockyard which is now all embodied by Plymouth. It is Plymouth. And - he - of course we naturally moved with him. And that was where - I - my education went further - were further on you see, went there in 1903 - in June 1903, I didn'
t
 start school until the end of the - summer holiday which was the end of August. Oh yes, I had goes long holiday. And - I went to a - a - of course beard schools we called them then, they wasn't - they weren't, you know, secondary day, secondary and all t
hat sort of thing, they didn't exist. No. In on years - probably as Technical school would be secondary school. Anyway -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did you live in Plymouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did we live then? Well I actually lived in Cecil Avenue at first near to the school I w
ent to and then we moved out to a new part of - development of Plymouth to Old Park Avenue, Old Park Road I should say which was on the Old Park Estate. That was being developed, about time, having new roads. And - I suppose I lived in Cecel Avenue, what 
- two years, eighteen months - two years at the most. And then I found it more convenient to get a - furth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
r afield and that was that. That's where we moved to. And then if - from there I came to Gillingham Kent. But still, in between times you'll want some more information won't you or will you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How long did you stay in that house in Plymouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Nine and a half years roughly. In October 1912 I actually left. I knew that. Either - either October the sixth I think 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Then were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I went -
 we came to - to Gillingham. My father and I went into lodgings. He was - further promoted to come to Chatahm Dockyard you see so we - he - he and I went into lodgings whilst the rest of the family were - waiting for us to find - father to find a home for
 
them and I come - I had the - left school obviously at that time and I was employed as a employed in - as a ship, yacht and beat builder. I had a shop first and - I - found employment, well I had already got employment already placed for me on the River M
e
dway, at Rochester. So when I - that's why I came up with my father from Plymouth ahead of the others, of the others. And - that - started towards my tenty - twentieth year then you see. 1912. Right. 1913 I'd be twenty-one - I remember my twenty-first bir
thday well. Anyway - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So you stayed in lodgings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes. Yes, the family came up several weeks afterwards anyway, a very short time, it doesn't really mean a thing does it. Not in that sense. There's a - got a lot of elimination to do here you 
know. Anyway, coming - coming down to other point of view of movement - of course they all had to go in lodgings when they first came, then my father got a house near our park and we all moved up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you give me the address of that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes. I was going to say, 32 Cleve Road, I believe it is. At that time was, you know, very well - I was going to say very strongly connected in political - local political world he was at that time, no not that time, yes he was, when I got married he was
 but not when he moved there of course. Became a town councillor but - of course, I'm a - I'm bringing my father into it now because - because you see he was a man of vast experience and - in public life one way and another. I've moved - I've moved from P
lymouth to Gillingham, I've told you were I've lived in Gillingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Then you got married from that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 From that house, well from my wife - from that house I went about ten mile for the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did you move when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well I took my wife up the Naval base up in Scotland where - up there. I got there before she was, I came down to marry her and took her back with me. I was up there - oh a good twelve month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where was that base?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I actually - the Invergordon mail base on Murrayfirth but we lived about two and a half miles outside, a place called Thorpefirth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You were there for one year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 We were there for one year. We lived in a - in a crofters cottage, walls about that thick you know. Pump ou
tside to pump the water. Just over the roadway which was the Great North Road and into the - into the firth and that's how we were situated. We got a - a little cottage, single storey you know. And eight years ago that was still there but had a tin roof o
n it and that was a garage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You went up to see it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Sentimental. Nostalgic. Anyway - and that is - this is - finally.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And you stayed there for a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 A year. Now the wife was having our first child. We came back, she came back before 
me, I stopped on a little longer and I came back and joined her and - and I - back into Chatham dockyard Naval dockyard. After that - of course we were in the midst of - first world war, 1918. Whilst we were there, up at the Naval base we saw some results
 
of that war in as much as we saw one of our cruisers blown up. H.N.S. Natal. We saw her come out of the water - lift - oh I don't know - half of the crew were lost, there were a party of children from the shore, I suppose there was a hundred and fifty chi
ldren and - young people and children aboard having a Christmas party. We - we saw it happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It must have caused a terrific stir in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well they - it did so because I - I was working up in the - up in the King George V another battle s
hip further up the harbour. We heard this terrific bang you know and - three explosions actually. We gazed down the Firth and we could see this - plume of smoke rising, then we saw this ship go up in the air and start to heel over one way and then go righ
t
 over and - we were on a floating dock up there, we had to sink the floating dock down to water level to - to - nothing should happen, the battleship was in it and we got ashore and I chased off to see how mother was, my wife - and - I passed people in th
e village being taken down to the jetty to watch, get what information he could, he was stopping at the big house but - oh - no, doesn't matter anyway -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was it a party of local children that was on board?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes, yes. They were there to entertain the local children from - Cromarty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It must have been a terrible blow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
It was. Yes. Yes. Anyway it was put down to spies you know, some traitors. Anyway that - that's what they thought and I still think it could have been because some of the things happened, not only there but in other parts of - Naval bases. However -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How long did you stay in Chatham after you'd gone back there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Chatham. Well - yes I'd been to Sheer - I had - being war time and one thing and another, I went to Shee
rness for a period just for a month or two doing work I was moving myself round with others. Mother, wife, still remained at home. I had to go to various other places where my - services were needed and - including - I came even this way, right at the end
 of the war I came this way to Harwich on the - what they call the Harwich Patrol out of Harwich Port on repairs and that sort of thing. But anyway that's - and that led me up to 1919.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where was your wife living during that time when you were traveling round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh we had our own home, yes, that's right. We - we - we - first of all of course naturally when you're - when you're first married you've got to find somewhere to live and - we had rooms somewhere, well of course that doesn't matter really, 
would be such small concern. We were able to get a house, somebody who had lost his wife and his - was emigrating abroad and letting his house for a short while, eighteen months and then we moved up to - took a house on the - Watling Street on what is now
 
the A.2. And - we had from - 19 - 1918, so from 19 - 1915 - Scotland, 1916 I worked Gillingham but we moved out of Gillingham across the road into Chatham, now that - this is one of the peculiarities of boundaries you see, there about a pavement outside t
h
e curb is - and the lamp, street lamp outside, all - oil lighted mind you - no it wasn't - they used to pull the - pipeline for the gas come up through the - the mantle - and - they used to do outside of our house, the lamp, well that came under the borou
gh of Gillingham which we'd just moved from into Chatham. So - one of the pecul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
arities of boundaries. But - anyhow, that is something that - that I come to now to a stop because 1918/19 as I say I was at varying degrees of employment, I wanted to get away 
from four walls of the dockyard I wanted to get experience further afield and I went - I went in the Marine Service in 1920 - early 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I just want to got some details about your family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh - what my family as they are now? My - my father and mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You've told me why you made most of the moves you did but why was it that your parents moved out of Portsmouth into the outskirts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh because - the - well the environment wasn't all that - it's more like going from the - Shellhaven near 
- meanest streets of Colchester and comin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 g out to the suburbs. Became su}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
burbia that's what I mean, that is the reason why, oh you see father bought this house and the one we were living in apparently was rented so he bought this one which was near to Ports
mouth football ground actually and all new estate thereright on top of football ground which I used to scramble in sometimes free of charge when the policeman wasn't looking. Anyway -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So he was providing a better place for his family to live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Ye
s, yes, that's right, yes. He - he - you see, he'd attained promotion. Obviously his income was - was increased so he - able to - buy or - or install us into a better - in the better type of home really. That is what boils down to. The old - terraced type
 of home that you got in those days where you - where you walked off the pavement into the - into the front room was gone then, you go the bay window and little bit of front gar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612 de}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 n you see, which all came about added the rough look to the place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I - have - I know eight of us in family so must be five brothers and three sisters. Four brothers and three sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Five boys including you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Five boys including me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I want to know their names and the order in which they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh well - I may - I told I've you I've got five - I had five - I had six brothers but one died, I remember him dying when we were youngsters, when we - I was about - he was about five and I was about six or seven but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I'd like to know where he came in the order of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes, within - within the order of sequence. My brother - let's see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 The oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Now you know you've got a hell of a lot of writing to do here, this is the day
 of age - of age when they used to give us host names for Christian names. I mean - a number. So had the wife and all too. We've got three each my older - older brother and my - myself. Well he's alive and he's - he's eighty next - in September And he's s
ix foot three, very athletic but - quite likely, yes, yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, now - Horace Albert Harry. H.A.H. H.A.H. Horace Albert Harry.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 He's the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 He's the eldest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who comes next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yours - yours -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How many years were there between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 A year and - ten months roughly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who came after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
I always argue this with my sisters as to who came between us because Bertie having died and my other brother that I told you died when I was about six they - I take - I - he must have 
been older than my sister Gwendoline but - that's what I think. I only know him as Bertie and that's as far as I know because as I say dying as a child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So Gwendoline came next did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Gwendoline.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How many years after you was she born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 They were all - on - on dates of birth now dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Gwendoline was about three years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who came after Gwendoline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 May. May. May would - she'd be much about - very much about two years between. I - I thi
nk you can say almost a cycle of two years really, the family came along. I think - say she'd be - she'd be about - she is still alive - she's - she's seventy-two I think. And then - come my - brother Harry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Another Harry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, well you see that'
s the - the composition of that first name of my oldest brother - my elder brother I should say - is such that it involves actually - three family names. My oldest uncle - my father's older brother was Horatio, he was called Horace. My father's called Alb
ert - Albert Edward. An my mother's only brother was called Harry so you - you have - obviously the first son that came along - Horace -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And they repeated them later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. Yes, they are because Harry - Harry is - repeated after that as a first nam
e - first Christian name. Yes. Anyway - he - he's seventy - seventy-one. Yes, seventy-one last birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Then after Harry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Reginald - Reginald Fred. Reginald.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And after Reginald?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Alec. And - and after him Cicily - Cicily Irene. God knows how they got that name but still - yes. Got the lot now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How old was your father when you were born, do you know roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Now let's do a bit of arithmetic shall we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you know the date when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I know the date when he died 
and I know he died when he was seventy-six but I also know a better date than that. It was nearer to his birthday which was early April 1925 he was sixty. Now you take that and do your arithmetic on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did he come from originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well he was a Portsmouth man really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 He'd been born and brought up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes. Of course I could come back further in the background and I can go back to 1790 but - but thereby hangs the tale you see, I saw something yesterday in Colchester that rather shook me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
What do you call window, glass window in St Botolphs Priory in the church, priory church. First thing we walked in the porch was glass panel there was my name at the bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Your own name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 My name. Waldegrave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your family come from round here originally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
We don't know. Waldegrave were mentioned in several publications by Alice Seaton. I think it is - following the Pilgrim Fathers when they were going across the water to - and she was from
 - well this - the heroine was a - a person who was being brought up in a household where there were certain other bodies you know and of course they were more or less Puritans rather than anything else, the pilgrims. You've still got that on haven't you?
 
Anyway - but - that - that name of Waldegrave occurred several times in the book and - they say there - and young William Waldegrave hadn't turned up to - for the dance you know, they were going to give this dance for the harvest or something like that an
yway and led me to think that either Suffolk or Norfolk, in that area. But - of course the - the family - the family name exists and - Teuton Mendip is the home, family home in Somerset. And - and funny thing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What is the tale you said hung}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13787969\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
