\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did this mean that he didn't have much time at home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well he - seemed to be always to to - 
to this that and the other you know. Mind you when he was home he was busy all the time you know, be doing, you know, secretarial work at home and - or - or slogging up some information, for his way you know, books. And he - he - you know, used to like bo
oks. He could recite poetry too. Yes. Tennyson Dreamlands and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 He didn't do any cleaning of the house then or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 On his retirement he did. Oh yes. Our - I always followed suit. And Michael does likewise. I say Michael does likewise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did he ever do the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I expect he did. Yes, I would say he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You don't actually remember him doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. Well of course you don't take much notice you see when you're a child do you. I say he would, yes, 
I say he would. He'd take - he'd take the weight off when he was at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would he be in charge of the fires in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh he - he would be very keen on that. Very keen on fires because - having so much to do with smithery work - he woul
d be aware of dangers of fire and well as the - as well the necessity of fires you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember if he was the person who always saw that it was in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I think he - I think he always got it - I think he always got it - clean
ed out and - I'd say he would because he would - he would - it was his perfunctory way of doing things you know, he would have it done. He was an obstinate man you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would he do repairs on the house do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. I think he would. I think he would. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - perhaps she wouldn't approach it. No, perhaps you - perhaps there wasn't any real improvements - let me see, wait a minute.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That would apply more when he moved to his own house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You think he'd be more likely to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
He'd be more like - but of course he'd gone - he'd only just come into the house, we'd been there about eighteen months as I said before he went out to the Cape. But - he'd taken on this church j
ob you know as sides-man of the church and general orgasiser of this, that and the other at the church that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How about dealing with the children, did he dress or undress the children when they were small - was he that kind of man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't think
 he would - he might, he might - he - he's funny - was funny in some respects. Mind you he was - what can I say - I have called him some names in my time but - very strict. He was very strict, yes. He - he would - oh he'd take us for walks. Yes, I remembe
r him taking us for walks round the Milton shores for walks on Sunday afternoon. With mother of course. Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did he ever take the children out without her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Not necessarily - I don't remember that because as I say - we would - our - our ho
liday time as far as we were concerned was August. The other time we left more or less to ramble on our own and - holiday time we went over to the Isle of Wight were my - maternal grandparents had retired, from the Navy here and - had a lovely little home
 
in Cowes. We used to go over there for - such as for this next three weeks like, Cowes regatta week and - and all the pertinences of bank weather, all the fun of the fair, all the royalty of Europe there. All the big yachts of - of all nations in Cowes Ro
a
ds. I used to go down when we used to go down to grandfather to the royal yacht squadron which has been much in the news today when Ted Heath not had - hadn't quite got elected, not from now 'til February, he - he stays down there with one of his old ship
m
ate who was the steward of the royal yacht squadron and we used go down and stand by the flags standard. The steward used to say, come on son. And we used to - and out past the bunk and up the - get ready flag five minutes before the start of a race. Eigh
t
 o'clock in the morning. 'Course all those - have you been to Cowes at all? No. Yes, well - did you go round by the royal yacht squadron? And saw the - saw the canon and the royal salute - twenty-one - they all used to be fired by touch - with a touch lig
h
t you know, manual - manually applied, not - not that are now from an electric button up top but - they were all fired you see, stand and we used to think that was fun you know. Well they were our holiday and we come home with a pair of boots each, ready 
to go back to school. I do remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were there special times of the year when you were bought clothes like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well that - that is - that is - the one - one example of what happened you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Can you remember your father telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, I - I can't remember him telling us stories now you want to ask my - my wife about that - her - her father used to - tell them - tell them story after story.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your father read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, now he - now he would - stand t
here and recite poetry to us, yes. Yes. And he could sing a song too. You know, the old type of - come into the garden Maud. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have musical evenings as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, I don't - I don't remember, no, -o. No. I don't think we really had 
a - a wasn't really enough time and family - we were growing up and growing up all the time and - I suppose the pressure of that sort of thing, looking back on it, must have been tremendous on mother you know, that those sort of things couldn't really hap
pen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she ever get a chance to go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Oh well, I say oh her own - I should - I should - must have done. I suppose so. Although I can't see how -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 If she did do would your father have looked after the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I k
now what you're getting down to, who looked after us. No, I can't remember any aunts coming in to look after us. Actually I can only remember two aunts on his side. And - of course -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Your father certainly wouldn't have you don't think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't t
hink - as I say one of them my father took - took charge of when - when the - her - his mother died and came with us to Plymouth. The other one, she was a young person. She may have come in. She may have come in. I don't quite remember tell you the truth.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I was interested in case it was your father looked after the children when he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, I've got no specific thought toward that because - I'm afraid that we - my brother and I, we used to get out - ourselves, not late mind you 'cos we were never allowed out late but - we would go down on Southsea Common and \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 football or play football in the season, well in or out of season actually, or else go up Eastley say and just swim in the summertime, or bathe - I couldn't swim in those days but bathe.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Just sometimes go and do a bit of shopping. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You didn't have special tasks like cleaning things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, no, not - no, I never had - no. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When would you do the shopping if you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - I remember going - we used to have a little trolley cart, you know, one of these home made box things with a couple of wheels on, used to go down - 
right down into town and be the main Commercial Road of Portsmouth, go right down there to Pinks, and they still exist, Pinks, Pink Brothers, the family grocers, go in there and getting large pots of plum jam, I think they were three or four pound jars, I
 
should imagine they were. I know you could get for about a shilling or something like that you know, tremendous. Difference in price of jams and that sort of thing but - I remember that sort of thing and getting - and going round into Flatten Road and the
 - the greengrocers and that and getting vegetables for us - my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you go on doing that when you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 'Cose we - we only lived in the two houses - the two houses I can remember in Portsmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you carry on doing the shopping all through your childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - I suppose we had our one or two - of course we mustn't forget that - well the girls weren't all that after me either were they. No, couldn't. I would say that I'd got sisters coming along but they - they were - not qu
ite so mature as us were they. Let me see. I suppose we went down into the town even room there. From - did you know Portsmouth at all? Now can I - put it like this - did you know Flatten Station? You don't. It was quite a - quite a long way. It's more in
 
the country when we lived there you see but of course it's all built up now. They've got Jesus Training College right where I used to be and all that type and all that sort of thing quite handy to where we were but - anyway - no, well I can't quite explai
n it but anyway - I daresay it was a - mile, mile and a half which to - it was to - to us was - was quite a distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You did it at Plymouth as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. I can faithfully say that because when I was the higher grade school at Plymouth mother us
ed to ask me sometimes to bring up some kind of butter from the Maypole. And I used to get it at school time - school break - when we went - when I went home, I would take it home. And we lived well out then. Quite a - quite a walk out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you go on doing the general shopping though when you were in Plymouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, of course you must visualize this, that I was then growing a bit and the girls were also now becoming a little older were they not.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your brothers and sisters have their special jobs which they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - brothers and sisters, let me see. I suppose my sisters had various jobs, must have done 'cos I suppose my mother must have struggling my elder sister in - interested in - sewing because my - she was - lovely needlewoman my older sister who died.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 But you can't remember them having fixed tasks which they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, I can't, you see we - when you're young you're in between ages aren' you, like neither one thing or other and - at school, as I say, this - I - I was onl
y in this board school for - the period of the autumn tern and then I passed my, what would be termed these days, 11+ exam, I passed to go into the higher grade and went the higher grade there in the following January. January the fourth I can remember, 1
904. I remember dates up to a point. I stopped there until the - August - end of July beginning of August, starting the holidays in 1907 when I was in my seventeenth year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You were quite old then when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I was. Yes. I had the opp
ortunity, my father offered me, although we - I'd got six behind me, brothers and sisters, well if you like, he said, I'll keep you at school if you want to - I'd got really good marks for - for science and - inorgan inorganic chemistry and that sort of t
h
ing. I said, I wasn't interested so much in - too much of the maths you know, like that, but chemistry I - I was really; interested in and I got good marks over the country from the results that came through from the Civil Service examination that I took 
a
nd - he wondered whether I would care to remain - I'd already got my sights set for this exam, I was mature enough to think, if you stop at school you may fail and could possibly have repercussed with in the family circle at a later date. That - that's my
 
reaction to this. I said, no, I'd soon go - have - have a job. He said, right, he said, I'll get you one. That's when he got me an a - an apprentice, Cross and Cole. Then across the other side of the harbour in Cornwall under, you've never been to Plymout
h
 have you. No, well, of course Plymouth is divided from Cornwall by the River Tamar and - that's the boundary line of Devon and Cornwall and just on the further side as you go out Plymouth Sound is Mount Edgecombe so and that - manager of the estate and I
 - ship yacht and boat building yard there and I - learnt the craft of that. But anyway that's coming - that's dodging the point - the issue. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You said you felt in between ages, not quite grown up but not a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes, that - yes, sayi
ng about whether I - I was carrying on doing - I would think so because I was - I was - shopping - I was stopping on late at school, coming home late at school. I was - later going back to school after tea and it was quite a walk from where I was - I shou
ld say a twenty minutes walk backwards and forwards each way to get to school. No, I should say no, I don't suppose I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You mean you don't really remember it or the rest of the children were doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, I wouldn't - I wouldn't because I - I would say say more self interested. Put it down at that, one of my characteristics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Can you remember if the older children in the family helped the younger children with tasks, can you remember helping your younger brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh - oh I
 think I - I - I can up to a point but - I remember taking them - taking them out in a pram, they called mail-carts sometimes in those days. You have, well remember - and tipping them over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 On purpose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, no. God forbid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you dress them or undress them do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No. No, I wouldn't do, no. No, I think they were getting, they were pairing up one with the other, while - of ages I suppose really - pairing up sufficiently enough to be able to help one another at that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think Gwednoline and Mary helped with the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I should say they did. Yes, I should say they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did the little ones help the older ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Help to give then excitable house sometimes. No, I don't - no, I don't expect they did. I doubt it. One way - one way traffic.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you were at school was there a certain time when you were expected to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Nine o'clock was our bedtime in a way but we were allowed a little extra but my father was stickler for ti
me. Bedtime and - bedtime it was but - if you had a - a subject you know you got stuck on it, maths wasn't all - wasn't my great furore in anyway I - I thought myself - and I used to puzzle over this, now am I doing right, perhaps I might spend half an ho
u
r extra on particular problem but - other than that - I never did - I - my father's - an advanced teenager - an advanced teenager, well you put that down because that - that is when we started going out and taking an interest in what father was doing. Joi
ning the Junior Imperial Constitutional League
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was there an extension on your bedtime then later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well of course there was you see there was always a - an excuse was there not finally because when we - my father - I told you politically minded, h
e was very - very friendly with a lady Asquith - Lady Aston and all that - Lady Asquith before he inherited his title. You see he was the Hon. William Waldorf Aster and he became candidate for the borough of Plymouth. Well my father was the agent for the 
T
alasop division of Devon that's where the urban part of Tavistock came into within the boundary of Plymouth for Sir John Spear, he was the agent for Sir John Spear and - and - my father organized the - these mass meetings in Plymouth for - for Astoth and 
w
hen he put up for Parliament and - they got very friendly, as a matter of fact, they took great interest in my father and - one way and another. However, what I was going to come down to was this that - we - founded the - room in the borough - a branch of
 
the Juniors Imperial Constitutional League whose founder was Viscount Castlereagh, Irish man, yes. Well, anyway - we became the first - the initiators of it in Plymouth. I was chosen for ward captain, my brother was ward captain somewhere else and - we go
t - got our meetings together, all young fellows you know up- up to the early twenties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 This was after you left school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Affer. And - we - of course boating is very interesting down that way - you know, the West Country, in fact the - 
any organisation has got a boating club attached to it. See we thought, well we'll have a boating club. So - ask the girls for five pound note, he said, well get yourself one. Five pound note mind you. I've been - I've been up to apprentice recently to th
e
 boat building trade was deputed to look for one. Second hand one of course. So - and I - I started to look round and I heard of one up the River Tamar, an old ex-Naval boat. I got all my committee together and we went up and had a look at this, I don't -
 
you know, about that much clear of the gun-whales, it was all full up with water, the boat itself, which is a very good thing from - from a maintenance angle because - because you should always take the plug out of a boat and let it sink when it's got to 
b
e left idle. Never pull it up a shore it's got to get it cover it so that you get the weather comes in and attacks the - attacks the planking. Oh yes, keeps off. Well anyway, I said, well - the person that was selling and I said - well - how it is for tig
h
tness? He said, oh it's all right. He said, I'll get a couple of buckets and go out and bale out, you'll find she's all right. We did. We pulled it in alongside, got these buckets, baled it out and got it - got into it and - we found that - well we didn't
 
know how much we'd left in of the water really but we left a little drop in I suppose, but she didn't seem to be lacking any water for - for a little while so we decided she would - would be all right with a little bit of repairs by yours truly etcetera, 
h
ave a look around it. So he said, well going to have it? I said, yes. Two pound ten. Fifty shillings. I said, right. I said, well what - what about - what about paddles, you know, oars. Oh he said, yes, here you are. And a boathook. And gunmetal rowlocks.
 
And then - oh - yes, the chap off the lion - the - off the H.M.S. Lion, one of the old battle ships and he'd got the plaques on the barrel you know. Anyway they were brass. Anyway, we got in and we pulled about two and a half - three miles right round Ply
m
outh Hoe right round up the river Plym from River Tamar right round up the River Plym. We stood up there alongside the electricity works and - pulled her up high and dry and then we turned up. Next day we went down in the evening and had a go at her. Appl
i
ed a nice thick coat of black varnish, that's tar you know, and - let that soak in, then I carried out a few repairs that were wanted and - next Saturday we were afloat. All - all marry bright going out towards the breakwater. But anyway that - that - tha
t - well that comes back to - we were - what we were doing. You know, when we broke away from the strict father. How did I finish up like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 We were talking about bedtimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, going to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You said you went to bed while you were still at school at about nine o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 About nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your mother put you to bed or anyone else or did you go up yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Not - not in those days my dear, I became a little bit too old for that, mother putting me to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What age did you start putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose really we was probably sent to bed and we put ourselves to bed but I expect we slept two - two in a bed - the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 The boys would share a bed would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes. Well I mean to say the rooms weren't necessarily big enough were they. Way I described them to you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Can you remember in that house in Portsmouth where you said there were three bedrooms would the girls have had one bedroom together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Well of course there'd be only two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Two girls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would your parents have had one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 They would have one room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would all the boys be in the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I expect so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You can't remember exactly how it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No I can't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Which room would you have your bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I suppose we stood in front of the kitchen fire. The good old faithful way wasn't it in those days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh good God. You don't know do you. These are reall
y ticklish questions aren't they, it's bad as - bas as mathematics, become a problem. Yes, now how many. Usually Saturday night. Yes, yes. You could say Saturday nights or Saturday evenings after tea you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would that be just once a week then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Be once a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would the family take it in turns to have a bath in the tub round the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
I expect we - that would be a family concern really in - inasmuch that - you couldn't keep water continually on the go although you'd probably hav
e a range - cooking range - the old coal fire cooking range with perhaps two or three big saucepans on it you see. That's the only obvious way of getting your water because it wasn't piped hot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You would perhaps top up the bathtub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How often did you have clean clothes to put on, when would you get clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh - well - no, I couldn't - I expect we had them - to put on from our - after the bath you know or - ready to put on in the morning after you'd had your bath, probably we went to bed after we'd had our bath when we were younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 As you had your bath on Saturdays it's likely you'd have the clean clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, oh you always had clean clothes - always had clean clothes and best clothes my de
ar in those days. There was no - no going out in your jeans Sundays and - and Mondays you know. That's right isn't my dear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did the family eat, where did they have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh mainly in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was there any occasion when they'd eat in another room, in the front parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well I suppose - there'd be - perhaps on a birth day or - might have something - a special occasion when we had aunties or uncles visiting or anything like that it might, I'm only saying they might. The 
children might not be invited in to have it. The adults might have it on their own. On the other hand - you could say that front room could be more or less - a sanctum not invited until you were told you could. All right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember an occasion when you could go in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, not particularly, no. No not particularly, all I know is that you - you could say - Christmas - Christmastime you'd have - you'd say probably have - would be open.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where did your mother do her cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 In the kitchen. Where the range was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 She cooked on a range, she didn't have a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, no, no gas - no gas then. Oil street lamps you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When was breakfast eaten by the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh - at various times I expect. Where was it eaten When? Well I suppose just-just in time the - half what got up in time to go to school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your father have it with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, no, he was earlier, yes. You must remember that they started - they started work in those days at seven o'clock. Some - so
me started at six but - some working class people started at six but the average workman or craftsman started at seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you had breakfast which members of the family would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose - now what age are we referring to now. At 
school. Well I suppose there were those that were already old enough to be going to school as well as me, I should think that would be logical way of answering that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were the younger brothers and sisters present, the ones who were not yet at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 They - maybe, yes, could be because they may be sitting up in the - the - the baby chair you know, with a tray on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would your father make his own breakfast or would your mother have got up to make his breakfast for him when he went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I should think my father would make his own. Same I do mine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What did you usually have for breakfast, what did you eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh in those - these - those days, well I suppose it was - mainly bread and butter. Mainly bread and butter, no such
 things as cereals then. May have been - I suppose it could have been the old fashioned oats but I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you have an egg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I suppose on rare occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would that be on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Quite possible, quite possible. Then
 not always, no. No, you might - you might sometimes even have a - a little bit of fried bread in - in bacon fat, you know, which was rather favourite. Which would be - which would be a Sunday. Sunday thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What did you drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose - water. No. No. tea. I expect it was te, I - milk wasn't so prevalent with us, no, not like it is now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You'd have something special for Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh for - for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I was thinking for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well no, I don't suppose
 really. I don't think you would really have any. As I say - mother and father might have - a rasher of bacon or - much as ever, much as ever, there wasn't - there' wasn't the type of thing that - the working people had in those days. I tell you what - wh
at was favourite though amongst working classes was bread and dripping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You liked it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I - we still like it now don't we with - pepper and salt on it. You get the right - right beef to make dripping or pork.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you mean that your parents sometimes had different food from the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
I don't think so, I think it's more or less communal you know as far as - far as we were able - according to ages I suppose we were given food that they thought was sufficient for us and - with e
nough nutriment and - I suppose they probably had something a little more I don't know, I wouldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What time did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Midday meal would be - well if - it was - a school-day, it would be - of course father wouldn't be t
here, naturally. School-day I suppose would be well after - as soon as we've all got out - home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That would be soon after twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Soon after twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What sort of things would you have to eat, can you give me an example of your midday meal, would you call it dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It counted as dinner, yes, not lunch. That's only a fabrication of a meal that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What sort of things would you have for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose we had - mutton because I know I didn't care for mu
tton in those days, I suppose we had mutton because that - that's something that does - otherwise I suppose we had - beef - poultry or anything like that was a rarity of course. I suppose, beef could be said as one of the staple meats of those days wasn't
 it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would you have anything special on Sundays for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well there again you see, pork could be a speciality because pork wasn't all that - easily come by or bought in those days was it. Pork was a - a meat that - people used to look upon as
 a sort of a - a change from the ordinary hum-drum beef. Now it's beef that's - quite the reverse isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would you have a sweet as well at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Might do on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 But not during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't think so. Might have a rice pudding - might have a rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would you have savoury puddings for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I suppose we had meat - a meat pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You'd have a tea would you when you came home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well, yes, I suppose you would say we had tea but yo
u know teas in those days - with the - with youngsters were more or less run about tea wasn't it. Piece of bread and butter and jam in hour hand or not - perhaps - no butter on it perhaps, bread and jam. No, I - I'm not joking. Bread and jam, I say butter
 was a - could be a luxury in some cases couldn't it. Yes. Yes. You'd run about perhaps and have it and - you - 'course father wouldn't always be there anyway so it wouldn't matter because he wouldn't be home from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 For the children would the tea be the last meal of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes, I - more or less it would be, yes. I suppose in some families they might have a biscuit to go to bed with but - I'm doubtful whether we - whether we had any. Might have a glass of water, we might have had a sweet or m
ight have had - you know, anything like kids will have you know, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you drink tea at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would your father have his dinner in the evening when he came in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, I think - well - now that's a moot que
stion because - dad started having canteens in the dockyard in those days you see. So he would have had his meal I should say, midday meal, in the dockyard. Of course now here's the point where those sort of things happened where parents used to send the 
schoolchildren to the dockyard with their father's dinners tied up in a red handkerchief, you know, the old spotted red handkerchief, like old Bill Sykes. Well anyway, that - that's a fact isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would the mother put meat and vegetable in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes, otherwise the father would take sandwiches in the morning it being bread and meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I never had to. Never had to. But I do remember it happening, I've seen the people there, even - even in latter years
, I've seen it since the - since the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When your father had his midday meal in the canteen what would he have when he came home in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Bread and pud. No, I wouldn't know really. I don't suppose we - of course we as boys, 
when you get a family of youngsters like we were, you wouldn't be noticing these sort of things really you know. There - there - it may happen where there's one child in the family might see all these things - sort of things with a certain amount of - rep
ercussions later. They say, well daddy has it, why can't I? You know, that sort of thing you know. We didn't notice it. And no beer. My father was a teetotaller.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Completely teetotal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, he wore the blue ribbon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was your mother a teetotaller as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes, as far as I know. Not - not - not in later years was she, she had a glass of stout, later years. And she used to have burgundy too didn't she, she used to have burgundy always, yes. My father was a teetotaller and a non-smoker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was that for religious reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well I thought he - I think he was brought up in a very cloistered - not cloistered, I was wrong word - very wrong word - his mother was a - rampaging - Wesleyian. Yes. Yes, yes. Grandmother Waldegrave was really a bit 
of a tartar and I remember visiting her as a youngster, you know, about so high, she'd sit in that chair you know with her laces and - and - and of course my father had a certain amount of that austereness about him in that respect of that sort. But - and
 
now you're coming back to this, you're also bringing me back in relationship to, when I was mentioning the Wesleyans. Now I went to the Wesleyan chapel, I was only that night, and they took my brother and I one evening to a revival service, they wanted to
 go down and pray for forgiveness and God knows what and frightened the life out of us. Us kids of about five or six year old you know. Ridiculous. And - it was - wasn't so very long after that you know we sort of packed up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Your father was a Wesleyan when he was young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was he still a Wesleyan when he moved to Milton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
To Milton. Well I suppose he was anything really, I suppose whatever - whatever his conscience dictated because - I told you he was a Protestant - an Orangeman,
 you see. Now he - he - whatever - he didn't care two hoots what it was as long as he was in something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your father or mother bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. Not to my knowledge, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Yes. Hom
e - jam was made very much in those days. More so probably than today when you - although you could buy it very cheaply mind you, when I say cheaply I - I thought I said the other day - earlier on - you'd get jam about three - three pound jar for - for le
ss than - less than a shilling, you know, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When she made her own jam would she buy the fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh she'd buy the fruit, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So she made it even when she was living in town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't ever remember recollect her bottling anything. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she make pickles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, I don't recall that. I - I'm the only that's ever done that since my married life I've bottle fruit and I've bottled - made 
- made pic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4683543\charrsid2370612 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
les, I do pickles onions every year, every season. Just a couple of jars so we got something - just for - myself or anybody comes in like a pickles onion well there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you do that when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, no, no, that - that's when I got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she make wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. No, as I told you we - we were more or less - teetotal family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did she make medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well, no, wouldn't make medicine although I've know my father make up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4683543\charrsid2370612 
sarsaparilla}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  which is - what was type of - - laxative I should think as well as being a refreshing drink and some kind of - jellup. I don't know - I don't know what it was but he}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4683543\charrsid2370612  - he - he used to make a concoction}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  with pearl barley and that sort of thing
. For - for - a sort of a - you know - a medicine of sorts. But of course, in those days - sulphur was one of the things mainly used to give children, sulphur tables and that sort of thing you know. Because it - th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4683543\charrsid2370612 ey could suck them, they were s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You liked them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose we had to like them, I don't suppose they were all that tasty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How did he make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 sarsaparilla}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well, there you are now, I don't know what the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ngredients actually was. I couldn't tell you, tell you the truth. You may - be able to look that up in some - some documentary evidence of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 
sarsaparilla}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 , I believe it's - could be - Italian. It sounds that way to me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 Sarsaparilla}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  it's spelt I believe, it's s-a-r.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you lived in Portsmouth were your parents able to grow their own vegetables or fruit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No. Not - not in Portsmouth itself. When we moved to Milton, I told you my father was very energetic man, we had a little allotment way out towards the marsh. And - he grew some then, of course, only 
for a short while you see. He had - he had to go abroad you see. That's only - that's only occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you moved again to Plymouth were you able to grow things there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, well - he was rather fortunate you see. I told you in the supervising c
apacity and some of the men under him used to bring him in - bring him in what he - what - I suppose, not to curry favour but - I suppose little jobs he might went and they could do and bring him fruit and vegetables at times from various places.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would he feel indebted to them if they did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - I suppose they felt indebted to him rather than - rather the reverse, because probably he'd put them on piece work or something like that you know. One can say it was wheel within a wheel. That's r
ather personal isn't it really in a way because - it's one of those little things that - you don't like to think that you're - well, living on charity although you're not. Re - repayment for - for perhaps a service rendered in a - in a backhanded manner.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You mean that way they were able to keep their pride?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think that was quite common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I think so, yes, I do. I do think so. I mean to say, you'll find - you find that - well, it's more like a question of barter isn'
t it rather than - rather than payment. Payment in kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It's rather curious in the work situation isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, in - in that respect, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When they weren't growing their own they had to buy it, apart from gifts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did he receive any other kinds of gifts of vegetables or fruit from relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, no, I mean to say - he had his - my old dad had his - had his pride and - of course as I said before he had that dogma that - that he was number one and if he was right he was right which has -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember having tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh they weren't known them days. No. Oh tinned fruit might have been known, I wouldn't - I can't - I can't say it wasn't but I don't know but - I - probab
ly there were - pineapples or something like that dried - or tinned I mean, not necessarily dried. Oh you had dried apples. Apple rings and apricots or prunes. They were - they were really a - a commodity you could buy practically in any grocers shop. Eit
her a little sack or in a little box.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your mother used them a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh - I don't know about a lot, I suppose whenever - perhaps on a Sunday we had stewed prunes, something like that, you know, as a sort of sweet. Of course - and then of course you had dried fruit like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 raisins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
, currants and that sort of thing which you make a - a roly - spotted duff as we used to call it, a roly-poly pudding you know in a - in a cloth and you could have slices of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That was Sunday food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Mainly Sunday, yes. I - I can't - I wouldn't like to say we had it particularly on - on any other day than Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were you able to keep any livestock at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. When I say no I say that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 reservedly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  inasmuch that my father obtained - a young goat whe
n we moved out from town in Plymouth out to the outer part, I told you went further out - we went further out towards the country, somebody gave him a goat. I know we used to take it out to graze. But - awfully smelly thing you know, so we - he got rid of
 it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You weren't able to get much milk from it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't suppose it was ever milked. No, I don't think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 The children would look after the goat would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That's what I tell you, we used to take it down - down to a pot of - plot of grass and let it graze a little while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How many times a week would you say you were able to eat meat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - it's difficult to say because - when you're going back, what - sixty-five - seventy years you know - of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  after}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 all - I
've got a fairly good memory but - you know it's a long long while isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I wonder if you have any sense of going without meat on some days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I - I haven't a sense of that really because - I've sense of knowledge of this much that I - we had v
ery little money because wasn't often we only had - wasn't often we had a ha'penny. That would be at the end of the week we'd get a ha'penny perhaps. You know, not - not pocket money. A ha'penny - well - that's run - running errands - running errand for i
t. A neighbour perhaps, might get a ha'penny from another person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You never got pocket money as such?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, not as such. Not - not as - not as children do today. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You didn't get the ha'penny from your parents ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. Not like - not in that sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would they give you a ha'penny if you did a chore for your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh they probably would. Probably would. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember anyone ever getting a rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, I don't - no I don't, now we - we weren't - we hadn't reached that point of starvation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 That was quite a w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 idespread habit in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, it probably would be. Probably would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, I wouldn't say because after all's said and done we were - an expanding family - of children. I suppose we was - we had what we were given and that was that. We wouldn't take notice of other - I know my father carved the joint and - on Sund
ay and that was that. As far as we were concerned that was our - our meal and - and the meat ration if you like to call it such and - I suppose if we were hungry we'd have a slice of bread and jam or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you remember noticing whether your father got a bit more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
I wouldn't - I wouldn't think so. No, I wouldn't think so. He would share it. I say, otherwise he wouldn't have been the character man that he was. That's my opinion now, you're asking these questions, I can talk wit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 h }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
m - what can I say - the with the knowledge of past with the present system of life. I say and not being a drinking man he didn't go out spending money in the public house you see. So we would be that way. And he would - he would buy - perhaps a Sunday - 
you know, sweets - weekend sweets for the children - for us children. So that - so that'd be instead of a ha'penny, see. A quarter or half pound of sweets. I mean to say when I told you they're four ounces a penny you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 During meals were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
I don't think so. I - I - I should say my father was strict enough to say, speak when you're spoken to, you know, or something like that, that - that type.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you choose what you wanted to eat or did you have to eat what you were given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh we had to eat what we were given really. But I - I didn't care for - I can - visualize some dinners I had not at home with my own parents but when I used to go to my grandma's - my grandparents - I never liked mutton. I believe I did. I di
dn't like that but - if you don't eat that you don't get any apple pie or plum pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
 or whatever it was. That was their approach to it. In other words - a threat. And - and then I think I made a - I made a - a gesture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you always eat up your mutton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well I did more or less, it's only in later years, and I'm not all that keen on lamb and mutton even now. Well I say, I have - we all have a preference for - for a particular kind of meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What was your father's attitude if you left food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I suppose he would have said, well, you can't eat that, you'll starve. Oh yes he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And your mother was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well of course }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 e'd have to - let father have his say. I don't say she was dominated by him but - I s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
ould say he was the stronger character.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask for it to be passed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I think it was always sufficient not to have to ask anyway. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Can you remember if you were expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, no, I don't think so. Table manners were up to a point but - as we looked upon it these days and - looking back on it I suppose we - we were 
more or less, what can I say, taught the normal table manners that any respectable household would - would have them. I wouldn't say we would be - capable of holding our own exactly in - in the highest of company but we - we could. You develop these thing
s
 in later years, I mean to say, by force of habit rather than foreknowledge. You see, if you can visualize what I mean, as you go out into the world and you - amongst company of someone in a higher sphere, not - not that - I - I say I'm as good as any man
 
personally, I've always said that, I - my - my way of life is as good as any other persons. My pocket might - may not be so large in spending capacity but - I would say that I can hold my - my own with these people. I wouldn't emulate their manners entire
l
y and - of course today you know, children they could learn a lot from the children of the past believe me, in table manners even because I - I - I'm on a Board of Governors at a school, I've been down there when they've had their school dinners, the chil
dren I mean, and you know, it's - it's sp}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 lling really. Of course, that's the type of household they're brought up in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You were definitely taught how to behave at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 We were taught how to behave. And had to ask to get down from the table too
, that's another thing which a child doesn't do so much these days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have to wait until the whole family had finished eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, no, you probably if they saw you fidgeting a bit they'd say, well you can get down now if you want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 But you couldn't do it before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, you couldn't do it before, no. Only if you were asked you know and were given permission. But that is - that is the - essence of childhood in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were you allowed to bring toys and books to meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh no, no, no. No, that's one thing that - well I do it occasionally at home now even I have certain amount of - you know - thought about whether I'm doing right or wrong. Just - have the paper on the table, in that - case we're talking about b
ooks, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When the whole family sat down for meals did you always sit at the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes, I think we would - we would observe that. Insmuch as, of course, various chairs were of a different character probably and - those place for father and place for mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 During the week you wouldn't be there fore a meal at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. Only on Sunday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was your father not there on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well you - you see, working days ended at - in some industries at twelve o
'clock on Saturday - I'm talking about the industrial world you know, and some cases at one o'clock. Now I - I - I used to start - when I - when I came as an improver to my apprenticeship I started at six in the morning and I didn't kock off 'til one on S
aturday. Half past five. Six 'til half past five and done o'clock on Saturday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So dinner time on Saturday you probably wouldn't be all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Probably not. Probably not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You said your father carved on Sunday, but for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 normal meals would your mother serve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes, yes. Yes, I - she would serve because - because father wouldn't always be there normal days you see. He wouldn't anyway be there at midday which was the main meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would she serve the food onto the plates and then pass them round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes. Yes, yes. No, do it - oh do it at the table. We - you have the vegetable dishes and everything on the table and you serve from that onto the plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So she wouldn't serve it out in the kitchen and then pass it round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Can you remember where your younger brothers and sisters would sit before they were old enough to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well they'd - when - if they were going to have a meal - a meal which they could digest I take it they'd sit in t
heir little - chair with the tray on it, you know, the hinged tray. High - called high chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who would feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I expect - one - I expect mother did really, I suppose as a child was able to lift a spoon it would feed it self, with a big.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you have re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5709036\charrsid2370612 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 memories of the eldest of the girls feeding the younger ones?
