bserving the fact that probably rent in those days was about half a crown, three and six a week. You see, which which, which I suppose - also coming back to - statistics, not necessarily statistics but - economics of building trade I should say the types 
o
f houses I've seen and - and we lived in one, I say were built for round about a hundred and twenty pound you know. And of course there were no rent restriction acts or anything like that to to stop people from being put on the streets. They had to be - i
f they had to be evicted they were evicted and that was that.
