 you see. I was never one anyway. And neither - I - I prefer to remain as I am, I don't want any kudos from anybody. I'd rather take my own way out, although I have been - often been a
ccused of being a freemason. Yes. I was speaking to my newsagent just before I came away, his brother's on the same board of - of Governors as I am, the school, and he was telling they were going to - to Spain and when they came back, the two brothers wer
