Yes. Jun - Jun - Junior Imperial Constitutional League. Well it was a unionist - concern, attached to the - of course the Tories - were - a mixture of Unionist and Conservatives. If you - if you can - hark back to them, I don't know - they we
re, I don't know from where it would be - would be - actually the head of of that particular - institution. Castlerae, of course he was Irishman. And - although we never met him. But of course my father would be - oh a public man. Although he was a dockya
rd officer he was a public man you know, and - that's how we got - became involved. We ran the football team, we ran the boating club in the summer and the football team in - winter and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So you had plenty of social life really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes, I did. 
I did. I also liked my - my - peritanacions you know out in the countryside. With - with two or three of the lads that were similarly - of similar nature to myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 There's Dartmor just around the corner as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I know, I walked from Plymout
h to Burrator and back - in an afternoon and early evening. Although I - I - I ran part of the way anyway, 'cos I was pretty fleet on my feet. Yes. I used to love Dartmoor, just over towards Brent, South Brent. I know that - I know - I know - I know Buckf
a
stleigh, I've been in the abbey several times. Yes, and I've partaken of the - the mead. Yes. I always think it's incongruous, that massive mill in front of the abbey. Yes. Of course they're still building there you know. I mean, where - about three or fo
ur - five years ago, we were last down there - down that way. They're building a motor way there at the moment, the A38 extension. Yes. Yes, but they're doing a lot of - bypassing I know.
\par 
