the various - homes at electioneering time and that sort of thing. As I say we took the horses out of the - out the carriage when Aster himself when he went in to Parliament. We took him out of the - took his carriage - carriage horses out and we put on d
rag ropes and pulled him round the town. You know, that sort of thing. Of course you don't get that these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 There's not so much specta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5785297\charrsid2370612 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
