Well I - I - I'll put it this way, my employers were such that - we didn't meet our actual boss, but only the foreman we met. The actual boss lived somewhere you in the - environments of Lond
on, outskirts - of the lights and they were also businessmen in the shape of - they had tugs on the river and that sort of thing you see, they were shipping people rather, but - apart from that - I got on very well with them. And we had a timekeeper - who
 
was round about my age there at the time and used to do - look - look at the time sheets and so forth - he was a - a young fellow about my age, and he done me - tried to do me - me a lot of good when I was out of work, and - in his later years. He became 
Secretary or the - of the Queen Line of steamers that operated here, the pleasure steamers out of this port, and also the General Stream Navigation Company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So he was in a position to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. He - well he was able to start - put me onto wo
rk. And - I've been to hide and - and got - excused from him to go back in the dockyards - if I wanted to. Well he appreciated my - my little bit of effort and the same as I appreciated theirs.
