y - under more modern condition now, you can weld a piece on I know and all that sort of thing. But with wood, you - you didn't have to do that, you could do it, gradually work it in. You see. As - with steel you've got to mould everything. You've got to 
h
ave - templates - to mark the piece of steel plating on, where it's got to form the shape of a ship. You - you build a wooden - with thin board you know and and put that out, or else - or else lay it out on a floor, on a - on an old log floor, and you wor
k out these templates, you make a templates what's on that floor, those lines, and you know, it - it's - it's amazing, you see a - a ship's side is like, taken from the centre of the ship down there and up like that. Well that's all - m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
