 Football League, we put a thousand odd players out every week on the field of play, and we're proud we do it. We have a splendid competition, we've got one - of the highest leagues in the county, and I've said, I'm not saying this boastfully because - I 
am only a - a nominal head now. I've been through the - the council and the shares and - and that, I'm just what they call - retired to the peerage. And - but I'm still as proud as ever, forty-five years of it and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You mean you got your pleasures in your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I got my pleasure from - yes. Walking, the wife and I have wal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 k}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ed thousands of miles, now that's not saying anything -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you do that before 1918, did you used to go for walks a lot in the period that we were talking about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes. Yes. Yes, I - now my - we had a very pleasant - episode regard of this - from the younger daughter of our two daughters. She said - she was talking to a young wives association at their church down in Hove down in Sussex, she said now I'll - always
 look back on my childhood with pleasure, when my parents used to take us all out for walks. And now moth - mother - mother was only talking about that last week. He was it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you started work full time did it change your relationship with them at all? When you grew up and left school and worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - I'm afraid sometimes we - we had a little blow up with another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You stood up to him did you as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. I was very - he had his - he was of course Secretary of t
he - Kent County Association for years, he was - dockyard representative on - the - the Admiralty for schools, dockyard colleges, and - many many other things. There - they - they're innumerable. He was council - town councillor here for - some years, but
 - I wouldn't follow politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Had you belonged to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. It was essential to be on - be - because when I went as a ships carpenter I had to either belong to the Seamen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 s Union or - an associated body, affiliated with them or - th
rough an affiliation, before the - at the time - what is now called the Shipbuilding - or Ship - Ship - Ship - Builders Federation - that was the Shipwrights Association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was it a closed shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I couldn't have got a job as a - as a ships carpente
r - perhaps on a - on a tramp steamer or something like that, but at that time, particular job I'd asked for - I wouldn't have got it unless I was - a union man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you take part in any of their activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I - I was a union man to this extent, that - when I was in the - estimating office, we were still - industrial at the start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 1943. '44. Yes. Yes. Well we were - we were industrial. We weren't industrial - until - 1953. But - in that time, we were also had an Est
imators Association, you see, from all the dockyards - in the Kingdom, and although we were only a small body of about two hundred odd, I was - I was on that - council and - we were fighting tooth and nail to get non-industrial - status you see. And there
fore - we were - being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 revivified}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
 by our own unions, my shipwrights association, and by the - AEF as is now, the - Engineering - Amalgamated Engineering Association - wouldn't play ball, inasmuch that they were - wanting - to have - represent us on a non-in
dustrial - they were industrial, we were - we were - we were wanting to be non-industrial, which we were. We - we don't touch tools. All we went round, look at a job and price it up and say well, that's our estimate of that job, and then we would argue wi
th the men who'd got to do it and say, well, if you can put a - put a case forward - where you could claim more, we'll - we'll - we'll review it, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You felt you were very much struggling with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, I - I - I went away, I went away - o
n various jobs, you know, daytime, I've been down to Witchford and down to the Isle of Wight or down to Southsea, and down to Plymouth on various schemes of work. But you see - this sort of thing - we had to build up - to put before the appropriate unions
 and their leaders. There's some information there that - rather staggered - stagger a good many people. There - there's my indentures. One shilling per week, sixpence a year after, and M was eighteen years old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How old were you when you signed this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Me, I was in my - seventeenth year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You left school when you were sixteen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I left school when I was sixteen. Yes. I could have carried on but my - I wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And this was the apprenticeship in the dockyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, I w
asn't in the dockyard, it was a small yard at - shipyard and boat building yard - down in well I used to have to go from Devon into Cornwall every day. Across the harbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you continue to live at home at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You didn't get lodgings in Cornwall?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, I - I used to walk say about - nearly three miles - in the morning and three miles back at night. Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What time would you get back at night then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Somewhere around about - around - somewhere round
 about quarter past six. There - there was a - a - as an active sort of fellow I suppose I was able to walk at least - four miles an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So it would take you an hour to get there and an hour to get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Round about, I had quarter of an hour's boat journey you see across the harbour. I used to allow myself three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 quarters of an hour really, but - of course you don't know that part of the world do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I do but not very well, I know Devon because I was living in Buckfastleigh last winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No. No. No, well I - I - I lived at - I lived at actually on the outskirts of Plymouth, I had to walk right into what was then - Plymouth was three - three towns once upon a time, not the City of Plymouth. Plymouth, Devonport and Stonehouse, and I used
 to have to walk from Plymouth to Stonehouse every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you find that taking a job for the first time changed your ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - you see, I - I've had what you call - respectable education, a little higher education than the average chap I
 was working with. We were practically a mob of - young apprentices see, younger than me. In - in age, but they were - been - been at the jobs - years - quite a little while longer than me. But - we mixed very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What about your parents, did they treat you as more grown up once you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - I suppose they did, I mean to say, after all's said and done one has to - more or less live in - live in that atmosphere of - growing up. And - therefore you know that's all. I - as I say I - \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 - had a - I chose this, rather than carry on at school, my father said, you can stop on, because at that time I was fairly good at - at - chem. - chemistry and science, but I wouldn't because we had five or six younger than me, six - six younger than me.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You were one of the oldest ones were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I'm next to the eldest, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did they treat you any differently once you'd left school and gone out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, no, I can't say - I can't see that because I - I lived my own lif
e in that particular way well I mean to say after all's said and done - one has to - accommodate oneself - to the - change of life in - in that respect only. Of course I - I mingled more - with different elements. You know, I - some of the rougher class o
f
 people in a way - if you like to put it that way - some of - some well - lesser educated than I was, I'll put it - I - I'm not - I'm not trying to be - you know, a high brow or anything like that, but - I - was - I - I was a higher - higher grade schoolb
oy as we were termed in those days, higher grade schools. And they were only - they were only ordinary board school boys. Of course you wouldn't - you wouldn't know about this sort of schooling, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I know a fair bit about it from my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes, yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Often when you do leave school you have this kind of - you change your life a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No - I - I - I - I - what I did really find that I - I - I got a little bit vulgar, put it that way if you like, in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 my - expressions of - I - learn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
t - learnt how to use a swear word occasionally you know. So that I'd call, you know say, you know, you're - a damn fool or something like that, I - I'd probably use a little stronger one as they - anywhere these days - one could say it's a word t
hat's - a household word, in most places anyway, but not in this one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I think you were in the choir and things like that weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you continue in the choir when you left school and went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you go to Sunday school still or did that drop off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh we went to Bible Class. That was connected with the church of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So that carried on after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes, I mean after all's - all's said and done you know 
- this may sound rather funny to you but you know - we still consider a Sunday as a Sunday. Both my wife and I, when we're away on holiday we always go to the church. If it - if it's possible to get there you know. Because that - that's been our life, I'm
 
not a religious man, not by any means - I think - as far as I'm concerned the church is - church is the whole - open - open atmosphere in which one lives one's life. I don't know how you feel about that but I - that's how I feel. Oh no, no, no, I - I - I 
maintained that interest right throughout the whole of my life. I've -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't know whether this is a country town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - it - it's - it's the biggest town in Kent. Oh yes. It's the - most populated, eighty-eight thousand in Gillingham, as oppo
sed to - Rochester next door - - sixty thousand and so forth, things like that. We have a population in the area - the Medway towns of around about a hundred and - a hundred and - eighty - hundred and seventy or hundred and eighty thousand. So - well we'l
l eventually be a quarter of a million in the course of another - decade - at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Quite a lot of children are sent to Sunday school when they're young and then when they get older and go to work -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, well that - then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Make their own decision on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Of course that - that - that depends on your -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You say there was corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, corned beef, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 But not much else in the way of tins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, not tinned, there was brawn wasn't there. You - you could 
buy - buy cooked meat couldn't you. But that corned beef was - pretty - what - what we would term in these days as very very cheap, it was around about eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 pence a pound wasn't it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were the children allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could they choose what they wanted to eat from what was on the table or just have what was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well they - they knew their table manners didn't they really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What would you attitude be if some food was left uneaten on their plate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh well - I think they were pretty good at - we - we knew their - appetites more or less didn't we, you know, so give them what - what was considered reasonable enough for them to eat without having to leave anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So it was gauged out anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Could they wait until things on the table, like the salt were offered or could they ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh they'd probably ask because it was usually on the table and if it wasn't near them, can I have the salt please, you know, well, a
s I say their table manners - were always - we always - taught them to - you know. To be just - behave themselves at table, they weren't expected to grab things and take like that because that's - that's - damned bad manners. So that's how they were - the
y were brought up, to respect table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How about asking for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I daresay they did occasionally, if it was something they liked, they had it if it was there to have, that's the point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were they told to hold their knife and fork in a certain and sit up in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What about bringing toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Very rarely. No, very rarely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When did members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose - they would g
et up - if - if - if we were all - all at table together - and it was approaching the time perhaps one might have somewhere to go, we'd say, yes, you can go, you know. All right - or - do you mind, you know, they they were brought up that way you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When the children were very young did you feel - there was a certain way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - the only way they were brought up was the way we would expect to bring them up, and that is properly. In - with regard to other people particula
rly, because if you have people in - in the house and you've got an ill mannered child there's nothing worse than feeling - if that child's not behaving itself you've felt the same perhaps if you've been in a person's house where there has been a child, y
ou know, you feel, well my child's not going to be - not going to be like that. And that is - as I say they were - taught to behave themselves. Not rigorously mind you, but just - quietly put in their place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think your wife and yourself had the same ideas on bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes, I wouldn't - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was there anyone you might talk to if you were worried about the children in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I - I don't quite - I didn't quite catch that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was there anybody you'd turn to for advice if there was - something, maybe something medically wrong?
\par <subject2>Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 W. Yes. Yes, my mother. I'd go to ask my mother.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was your mother alive when the children were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, my mother was alive but then 
you see - my mother was a different atmosphere to my wife's mother. Wasn't she, my - as I told you before my - my father was a public man, and - their lives were different - differently - placed to ours. I say, and although he didn't live so very far away
 from us, only - a mater of - several - minutes walk away - they - they were - more or less - in their own atmosphere. My father as I say was a - was one of the town council}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 ors at - on one occasion for quite a period of time and he had his - still had his 
- other - objects in view, you see, so many things he was engaged in. He dabbled in - most things. Therefore - we were - we were really not more - not so concerned with my people as we were with my wife's people. 'Cos my - my - father-in-law was a - a pro
per - quiet old fellow, wasn't he dear. Yes. You know, a gentle type of fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So really you kept more in contact with your wife's parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes. Of course my - my father was a very dogmatic man. So that - that's putting it - point blank, he
 was a dogmatic man. And as far as I was concerned I could go my way and he go his you see. But - we - we were best of friends and - oh yes, the best of friends but - that - that was the atmosphere between us more or less, you know, we're bringing up our 
family and that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you want your children to share their worries with you if they had any?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Share their what? Worries? Oh we'd like - we would wish them to. We would wish them to, oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What kind of things did you think you ought to do for your children, what kind of things did you think you ought to give them say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 In what way, material?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Like affection or safety, that kind of thing? Material possibly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - we - we could only give them what we could affo
rd to give them, that - that was - not all that much I may tell you, I mean to say - they - they - as I told you before, we - we we took them out with us and if we could give them a good outing - well they were happy that was all that was required of us a
n
d they - all they expected of us. Well as they grew older of course they - they found their own feet, they found their own friends. They go their - their way, as long as they were - behaving themselves that was as far as we were concerned, if they didn't 
behave themselves of course they get a damn good talking to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you were young did you both ever manage to leave them so that you could go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well, yes, the older girls didn't they. When - when - we never went out - while the other - when our
 - old - older children were young, we never went to - never went out or - we never had holidays or anything like that. As I say - mother had the - had the difficult task of looking after those children while I was away from home, as I was on those occasi
o
ns - at sea and that. But - other than that - when they - when they grew up, they were able to - just - take over the children - mostly Monday nights wasn't it when we used to go down to the theatre, you and I and Mr and Mrs Milner, we would - one of the 
girls would stop in and look after the younger ones, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 This would be quite considerably later wouldn't it, 1920's or '30's that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Going back to the first few years of your children being young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How did you want the children to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well we wanted them to trust us. Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, we liked to feel that they - they felt they could come to - for help. Oh yes, we liked them to trust us. Well they did an
yway. I don't think we - any of them would turn round and say we didn't do our - duty by them, can they, hit one of them, not - because - they're all affectionate to us still. And old as they are they'll come and kiss me, boys and the girls.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Were they allowed to speak when grown ups were talking?
\par <subject2>Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 W. Not when they were small, definitely not.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What kind of things do you think you brought them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I suppose - honesty of purpose. Do th
e best they can. They can't do any better. Play the game if they've - if they're that was disposed. Of course - the boys are - are more - what can I say - not quite so - I can't quite get the right word }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
meal - amenable to - to discipline as the girls w
ere. Not to that extent. Well you can understand that anyway. Because - there - there was a - a difference in age between the oldest boy - and - the next oldest - the next boy down, a difference in age, let's see, Dennis is 1924, - Colin is 1916 you see. 
S
o that - that margin of difference, you have two girls in between, you have that margin of difference between the two boys. Now that boy we used to take around with us when - when he was - when he was born - was - was a nice age, we used to take him aroun
d
 - 'cos I was a referee - a football referee at that time, and when I went round to various places refereeing - and mother was available, and we had referee's meetings, you know, and - that sort of thing. He always went with us. Outings, always took him w
ith us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would you say the children received their ideas on how to live from both parents or from you mainly or from your wife mainly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I think - I think - of course the wife has - had the major influence. There was no doubt about that. Wife had the major influence.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Some people think that children should be with the mother all the time and other think that it's not necessary, it does them good to be with other people quite a lot, what did you think at that time? Did you think the children sh
ould be with the mother most of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - no, I - I say - they - they were left to their own devices, when they became of - of an age - when they became of an age to be able to differentiate between right and wrong, then they were left to thei
r own devices. They were corrected when it was necessary to correct them. If I wasn't at home, as I say, when I was away and I wasn't at home, the - responsibility of that fell on the wife, naturally. And - and they always turned to mother, they still tur
n to mother for anything, don't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What about when the children had a birthday, would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, they had their little - little friends in and - they had a little party you know, just to - cheer them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What about cards and presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, used to play - play - normal games didn't they. Indoor games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What kinds of things would you do as a family on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Ah - now which Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 In the early years of marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 O
h yes. Christmas Day was our home day, when we had - of course wife played the piano. We still have it, she still plays it. But - we - we used to have - our song, 'cos we didn't have wireless then mind you, there was no - no - radio, and we used to have o
u
r little sing-songs, the children used to sing their little pieces, say their little bits of poetry and that sort of thing, they enjoyed their - they enjoyed their Chri - their little Christmas together - with us. Then - then - the following day, we were 
-
 oh we used to have the wife's - some of the wife's family up didn't we. And - on Boxing Day used to have my - my people - come up sometimes. But that was the - only - difference and the children themselves as I say - were - well right up - right up to a 
little while ago came in the grandchildren then wasn't there dear when the ceiling fell down in the other room with - knees up Mother Brown or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have any books or newspapers or magazines in the House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I always had - I a
lways had a daily paper, and a Sunday paper. Because I think it was - well it was the only way of keeping in touch with the - with what was going on in the world around because - you - as I say, there was - wasn't wireless you see. There was no radio. Whi
ch is one of the things that - has brought - brought one end of the world - right on top of the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Which daily paper would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Me? I suppose the - I - I - he's asking - asking for political points of view isn't he? What papers? Yes, wel
l I had the - I have Daily Express, I used to have the Daily Mirror. I - sometimes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 This is in 1918 time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 We had News of the World on Sundays, then we gave that a go by, had the News of the World because - every - every weekend they used to ha
ve - print a - print a song there. Oh yes, they used to print a song all - all in the music didn't they and the words, many a song in there. A song, those that were most popular too. Well we used to cut them out didn't we, for that - more or less for that
 purpose. Of course that was a blood and thunder paper. Well - it got too much of it. And I have the Sunday Express, I've had it for ever such a long while, but - the Sunday Express is a paper I've had I suppose - since - 1923 I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What did you have in the very early years of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - we used to get the Scotsman up in - Invergordon. The Scottish paper. Other than that I can't really tell you, except - except that - we got whatever paper was going, because going to work you didn'
t - you bought - you - you bought a paper at the gate, dockyard gate you see, whatever was going you simply bought a paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you get any books from the library or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, we belonged - we belonged to the library, we - we s
till belong to - Gillingham library but - we belonged to Chatham library then didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did the children go out with just you sometimes on your own or was it usually as a family group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh I did, yes, yes. I - I - I - I've got that snap of those
 horses up on the main wasn't it, the children, yes. Yes, the - I used to take them out. I - I've got a walking stick out where they've knock - knocked all the handle to pieces, playing hockey with it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you go anywhere on bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes. We used - if - if it was - we couldn't go far. But as I say, on those sort of days - we'd pack up a little picnic - lunch and - tea you know, and perhaps go over across - what they call Hucknall the other side of the river, or somewhere like t
hat wasn't it dear. In the main it was Upnor wasn't it, it was a fashion}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612 able place to go to, there you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
are, bank holiday. But - we used to go up the Staff there occasionally didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That's along the top on the A2. On the top roa
d. They used to have a fair there. There's an old charter fair - it was - it used to be held in the parish - by the parish church right down in Gillingham. As a little chartered fair it gradually - it went from there - when that was - by virtue of the fac
t
 that sometimes happened there you know - some - there was an alteration, and - they changed and they - it grew too big for the place, I'll put it that way. And they - they had it up on the - up on the A2. where - in there - where the - A2 is now but real
ly it was right through.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever go away for holidays as well as bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No. No. We never had no money to go away did we. No. No, we never had money to go away for a holiday. Might - might have taken the youngsters to the - the young
est ones - up to - either to Maidstone or - places like that on the bus and then gone up the river. But other than that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How would you spend Saturdays and Sundays, after you got married and had the first two children, did you do anything with the 
children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well you must realize that - there was still two years of war when we had the first child. And - and the other one came along, well there wasn't much that you could do - at that time. You were still in the - in the process of getting o
ver the war weren't you right up - in the early twenties, and that was when things were bad. I couldn't get a pick and shovel job when they were - doing a - doing a - alterations - widening the main road up top which came eventually as the A2. I couldn't 
e
ven get a pick and shovel job there, because - we were living - that much - in the - boundary of Chatham. Upon the A2, one side's Gillingham, one side's Chatham, as that A2 runs through, it still is. One side's Gillingham and one side's Chatham. We were l
iving on Chatham side and I couldn't get a job on the - Gillingham side. No relief - relief work. No. I was out of work eight - eight - seven months then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What was your attitude towards Sunday, and the children playing on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 The children all went to Sunday school. They all went to Sunday school didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What did you feel about them playing on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well I don't think they ever - I don't think they really had - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you think it was wrong to work or to enjoy yourself on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh no, as I told you - you know, I - we - we - did think and still think that Sunday's a different day to the rest of the week, and therefore - we try - or - we did try and we still try - to make that little difference - in our approach to the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You went to the Wesleyan Church in Gillingham?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Baptist, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you both go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, no, my wife - I didn't know my wife then. When I went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 This is all after you married now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, we - oh n
o, we were in a different parish altogether you see, that's right down there. And - the - where - where we were married, in Gillingham parish church. That's right - right down, still there, it's a twelfth - twelfth - thirteenth century church, you know, a
 twelfth century church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Which church or chapel did you go to when you came back from Scotland and lived in Granville Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 We still go down there didn't we.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You said you were in the choir earlier when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 That's before we were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you continue that after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, I didn't. No, no. No. My - my choir came - when I was abroad. I had two years in the church choir out abroad. But - other than that - I should - there - there was a - what else was there. Well, no, 
I didn't - I didn't do any other - choiring - choir work since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you belong to any clubs round by the church, like a temperance club or anything
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, I didn't. No I didn't. Other than what I told you about - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 These questions are all to do with the early years of marriage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No. No. No, we hadn't got time really, we hadn't got time, as I say, we were bringing up a family, and as I say I was - wandering around getting - getting a job where I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did your children go to any of the adult services or just to the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 They all went to Sunday school didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Was grace said at meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. I'm sorry to say no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, we - we didn't get down to that 
because I think that brings a child up in a narrow - in - into a narrow - outlook on life, you - you're ramming religion down their throats you know and if you ram religion down a person's throat when they grow older they don't want it. See, they - they -
 
if they've got - sense enough to - to - rebel against the whole idea of religion. It - it does - in my - my estimation anyway, what I've seen of life, that sort of thing does happen. Yes, you've got to - I think you've got to have an open mind. I think it
 essential to have an open mind on - on all - all topics. Whether its political, spiritual or otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It's easier to have a closed mind,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh - I - I - yes, well that - that - there's one - there's one factor that you've got to look at, you've g
ot to have faith in what you think. If you've got faith in what you think - the whole world can go bust. As far as you're concerned. In - in other directions I mean, you've still got to - you've still to to have - a - a - a - a fellowship with your fellow
 
man. Haven't you, I mean to say, you're still - still - you're still all inter-dependent - on one another, and if you're still interdependent on one another therefore you must feel compassion or - or hatred whichever way you like to - exercise your though
ts, you've to have - another - another combating force and that's faith in your own religion. Or what you were taught. Or what you think. That - that's one of the factors that people - try to forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have any interest in politics after your marriage? Did you vote for instance in a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No, no, no, not in politics, I - I have been a presiding officer at many polling booths that I can remember round this area, I suppose I've been in practically in every - in charge of every poll
ing station - I was going to say - in Chatham and Gillingham, In the past fifty years - when I've been at home, for both - county council, municipal and - Parliamentary elections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You haven't actually been organizing the counts and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh no, no, my politics is - I - I - I keep an open mind on those things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So you weren't a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever feel under any pressure to vote for any particular party because of your employment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well, yes, up to a point, yes, I mean to say you've got to have - if - if you've got to cast your vote you've got to have a - a - a motive for - casting your vote. You've got to think - you've got to think the issues out for yourself. You've either got 
to vote for the part - for a party or for an individual you see. And if you - if you - think - these matters over - you - if - if you don't vote at all, I'll put it this way, if you don't vote at all, then you've got no right to to find fault. With whatev
er happens, because you've no right to have a say in the matter. Because those people that - go - eventually go and - and represent the community at large are the ones that - put there by the people who registered their vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 When you and your wife were at a home how did you spend your leisure time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well - whatever leisure time we had, I - perhaps I - do it yourself jobs and so forth. Of course as I told you I was refereeing for twenty years, and - that's - weekends you see. Saturdays I mean, not 
weekends, because Sunday football hadn't so long been in vogue but - other than that - well we enjoy our - our company with ourselves. You've asked a question there which was asked by one of our neighbours, not so very long ago. We - we sit here and we ca
n
 talk. Wife and I can talk. We can - just read one word in the press, like this, do you remember that? So and so. Something - only a place. No, well what was that? Say, well we passed that when we were going up on the Al or when - when we were going throu
g
h so and so, and do you remember when we got so - and we go from one place to another - within time we're over at Guernsey or somewhere there and back to ourselves, and we can talk for hours on this. We talk for hours. There - is this year's diary, in the
r
e is only a few press notes - from beginning of this year up 'til now. I've got dozens of them. And we go back. If - if we can't remember, say, oh that wasn't - I say, right - back to 1918. Do you remember when we went so and so? And we can talk and talk 
a
nd talk. Do on another. So we're happy. The wife'll be doing her knitting or her crocheting - or we'll - have the wireless on, now - music - another thing you see, the wife plays - well she doesn't do very much these days because of the - well it's too co
ld in there in the winter and in the summer we like to go for our walks. You see. So this is this is the whole set up - as far as we're concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you belong to any clubs or institutes or anything like that in the early days of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No. Well, not those early days. When you say early days you - you mean the first -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Say 1918 - 1920
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - 1916 to 1918 was wartime, you - you were at back and call of - of - I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have any pets or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, no, not when they were small, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Until you became a referee did you actually play football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes, yes, I - I played football, I - as I told you I played football and cross country -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever do anything like bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Cy
cling? Oh I used to cycle, well I used to cycle regularly to - backwards and forwards to work, but - but not for - not for - not - not when I was married, to go out cycling. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How about fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Only fishing I've ever done and I - I can tell you this, is off Plymouth Sound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 It's a good place is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Yes, I've been there fishing for pike just off of Drake's Island. You want empty - once they start to bite you get - an empty hook'll catch 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did anyone outside the home help you or your wife too look after the home or family in any way? Like relatives or friends or neighbours?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No. No, when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Say your wife was confined to bed how would you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well, on those occasions - there was usually - I would be availa
ble in the evenings, and - well - thank God they were few and far between. That's the only thing I can say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 So you were able to cope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you have any friends that you saw regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 No, we knew nobody out that way did we, not Granville Road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How about when you moved to the top house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Well we - we - yes, one or two neighbours there, was quite friendly with, one particular one, Mrs Milner. That was about - she was about the nearest wasn't she although Mrs Randall Lewis - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever have friends come into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Oh yes. We used to - we used to go into her and come into ours, they were only next door but one like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 How about something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would there be any special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did friend call in casually or did they have an invitation to call round?
\par <subject2>Mrs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1198299\charrsid2370612  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 W. Well, you see, I had some sisters and - they'd come in or - Ethel - my sister-in-law, she'd po
p in any time.</subject2>
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Did you ever have a musical evening or any kind of evening with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
We did - now we did. We - we can say that can't we? We - Granville Road we had musical evenings. There was - wife's sister, her friend, Edie, ther
e was - the wife's sister's eventually her husband, he - he wasn't then, he was - he was - they were courting. Three other Naval fellows was it? Two anyway. Yes. They were - we used to have - violin, piano, two - they used to sing, they - Geoff used to si
n
g didn't he, and - used to have a musical evening in our front room down at Granville Road, when - when Colin was a boy, a baby - baby. That's our eldest boy, when he was a baby, we used to - they used to come in - fairly often, they were in the barracks,
 Naval barracks you see and they used to come up, have - have coffee and - a bit of supper you know. And then we used to have - enjoy those musical evenings didn't we. You know, Grace is going West and all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who did I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who were the most important people in the town or the are you lived in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Who did I think was most important? It's difficult to say isn't it. Well - not yes, I suppose so, I
 mean to say after all's said and done - he - he is the selection of the - of the people that you put in to govern you - locally isn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Most important bolke is the rate - was the rate collector.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 The rate or the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
No - no, I can't - I can't - really diff - differentiate between - the - much as I know - know of many many of the Mayors of the town, they were to me they were no more important than the man in the moon, in - in - only in relation to the office. 'Cos
 some of 'em I wouldn't give that much for. As individuals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what sort of people went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Well - it's difficult to say isn't it. I suppose really - there's the usual trend of - of th
eir own particular denomination, I mean to say after all's said and done you know, if you're Wesleyan - or non-conformist, I'll put it that way, if you're non-conformist, you'll find that there - there are more - together - than the established church. An
d
 therefore you get the type of people - going to a chapel who are - what can I say - more community. Whereas with the established church, I'm talking now of the - Anglican - Church of England - they're cliquish to the extent - of they're off, you know, to
 - and - and - really - cold, they're not welcoming. Unless you happen to be right at the inner circle. That's the type of people - I consider goes to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 And the more friendly groupy ones go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 You can't - you can't say they all had the same standard of living because each individual family must be - must - be - governed by the par
ticular incomes, and they're - their - upbringings, because after all's said and don}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13370131\charrsid2370612 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
, we - we happen to be of a family - we - we were moderate people - working class, yes, but brought up in an atmosphere - wholly our own. Therefore you can't - you can't -
 say well that particular class - that segregates us from that class because they - choose to go - beer drinking and public house and that sort of thing and - and - and have got - haven't got a penny to bless themselves with the next day and they probably
 
would have been better off than you, so you can - you can hardly describe what - where the difference is in working classes, I mean to say, working classes are working classes whether they're - artisans or - or - egg slingers as we used to call 'em, you k
now, clerks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think that one group felt superior to the rest then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Would I think what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 For instance you just said the artisans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Or the ink slingers, do you think that any one group out of them even though as you s
ay you can't generalize it, that they themselves thought they were superior to the other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes, yes. The white collar - the white collar person was superior to the - to the man in the overalls. That - that - that was the considered idea, alt
hough the man in the overalls was getting more money, in - in my young days - the average clerk - in a - Prudential office or somewhere like that was getting about a guinea a week whereas a - a mechanic, full blown - fully indentured - man, artisan - woul
d
 go and get about - thirty - thirty - bob to thirty three shillings a week. But - but - but - these people always were superior to you because they used to go to work clean and come home clean. Now that - that was difference, yes, I agree with you there, 
there was - there was that - trend, in - in - in the - the two -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think it was a reasonable thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 I - well - well I think it was a pompous idea myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think there was much distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Bet
ween craftsmen and labourers, now - that depends upon on your approach to - to the individual, after all's said and done - I as a craftsman - have a responsibility of work - a labourer - a labourer. He himself - has only to do as he's told. See, therefore
 
- there is - there - there's a - a distinction there, and therefore - a craftsman does claim - the right - to have what we would regard as responsibility payment, for our knowledge. Over and above the labourer. So - there - there - in that - never - never
 
look down on a labourer. A craft - no person, no person at all - should look down on a man in the gutter - than the - crowned head of England, because in my opinion we're all interdependent. Now this is only - because - I know I express myself that way, a
n
d I have done - often, I say, how are you John, or - or how are you, to a man in the street or along the country lanes you know what it is in the country walking along a country lane, meet a farm - farmhand coming along, goodnight sir. Goodnight, you know
. But - you know, old John, he puts his nose up like that, you know, how they do you know. And then there - that's the type of thing you'll meet isn't it. You have met it - yourself, most probably.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16392620 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 Do you think in those days that there were some families considered respectable and some families considered rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1141354 FW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484140\charrsid2370612 
Oh yes, there - there are, yes. They do, you do meet it because - you - you feel - when you see this sort of thing, you feel that - they should be in a better position than they are, beca
use it's not necessary for them to be in that position, and ninety-nine times out of a hundred it's brought about by their own - by their own self will. If that's what you mean. Because - they're respectable well does that - where does respectability lie,
 that's the point. I mean they - may be the biggest rogues in - on earth.
